@Node "Limit" "Limitations of Unregistered Version"

Limitations on the unregistered version are:

  · Song length is limited to 10.
  · The Insert and Delete buttons for position arrangement are disabled.
  · The MIDI-Filter window is disabled.

@Endnode
@Node "features" "MidiTracker Feature List"

@{u}MidiTracker has many useful features. Here are a few.@{uu}

* Dynamic @{" pattern size " link "pattsize"}.

* Unlimited number of tracks per instrument. 

* Supports all 128 controlsources.

* @{" Sample Dump Standard " link "sdump"} support so you can upload/download samples
  (8bit or 16bit) to your synth or sampler.

* @{" Controlsource Graphical Display " link "csources"} that allows parameter editing with 
   your mouse.

* Support for any synth you wish!  If registered users send me the SYSEX
  info I need, I will code support for your synth into MidiTracker.
  (click @{" here " link "synths"} for details)

* @{" Channelscope " link "cscope"} mixer to adjust the volumes of all midi channels 
  independently.

* Ability to import ProTracker and OctaMED MMD1 modules.

* Ability to import/export Standard-MIDI-Files (*.mid)

* Can handle @{" multiple songs " link "subsong"} in memory at once.

* A 16bit @{" sample editor " link "sproc"} to edit/upload @{" sample dumps " link "sdump"} or samples
  you get from CDs or the net.

* @{" Gadgethelp " link "onlinehelp"}  (Kickstart 3.x only)

* Many @{" Hotkeys " link "hotkeys"} for quick access to commands.

* @{" XPK " link "xpksave"} compression.

* Locale support (Kickstart 3.x only)

* An @{" ARexx " link "arexx"} port.

* @{" Stacker / Remapper " link "remapper"} to redirect midi data to different midi
  channels, create instrument stacks and act as a software midi patchbay.

* @{" Midi Time Code " link "mtc"} support.

* @{" Trigger Actions " link "keyboardactions"} by playing your keyboard

* Versatile @{" Midi Filters " link "MIDIfilter"} for both input and output.

* Can play @{" Samples " link "usesamples"} with additional Sample-player software!

* @{" Backtracking " link "playsong"} of controlsources

@Endnode
@Node "requires" "Requirements"

@{u}What you need to use MidiTracker@{uu}

* 68020 or better would be desirable, but a 68000 version is also included.

* Kickstart 2.04 (V37) or higher

* ReqTools library V38+

* A midi interface and midi equipment (synth, drum machine etc...)

* A basic knowledge of midi concepts

* Inspiration ;-)

MidiTracker should work with all graphic boards.

@Endnode
@Node "install" "Now your talking!"

@{u}Installer script@{uu}

Double click on the install icon and follow the instructions.

@{u}Manual installation@{uu}

1. Copy the desired catalogs into LOCALE:Catalogs directory. 

2. Copy the supplied libraries to your LIBS: directory.

3. Create a directory and copy the remaining files from the archive into
   this directory.

That's it!!  No assigns are necessary and by default the program saves
its preferences into its home directory.

To run MidiTracker from Workbench, just double click the icon. You may
adjust the @{" tooltypes " link "start"} if you wish, but take note that tooltype settings
have priority over settings within MidiTracker's prefs file.

To run MidiTracker from a shell, type "MIDItracker". If you want to adjust
tooltypes via shell, then you can supply them as @{" shell arguments " link "start"}.

@Endnode
@Node "files" "MT's roadmap"

@{u}Miditracker Directory Structure@{uu}

MidiTracker home directory
 |
 |-- [dir] Catalogs (optional) - multi-language catalog files
 |
 |-- [dir] Help (optional) - online documentation (this amigaguide)
 |
 |-- [dir] Synth (required) - definition files for the @{" dialog windows " link "synths"}
 |
 |-- [dir] Songs (optional) - default song directory
 |
 |-- [dir] Sysex (optional) - default sysex directory
 |
 |-- Controlsources - here are the names of all 128 controlsources:
 |                     4 chars = abbreviation for the @{" Src " link "src"} track
 |                     1 blank
 |                     3 chars = reset value 0-127 (for @{" panic " link "panic"} ).
 |                               Enter 128 if you don't want a controlsource to be
 |                               reset on @{" panic " link "panic"} or if you hit @{" Play Song " link "playsong"}.
 |                     1 blank
 |                     The remainder of the line is the full controlsource name.
 |
 |-- Quicksongs - this file is automatically generated. It contains the full filenames
 |                of the @{" quickloader " link "openquick"} menu.
 |
 |-- miditracker-key - the keyfile if you have @{" registered " link "register"}.
 |
 |-- @{" MT-MC-ED " link "mt-mc-ed"} - This program must be in the same path as the "Controlsources" file.
 |
 |-- MidiTracker.prefs - saved by MidiTracker.

@Endnode
@Node "start" "Tooltype Settings..."

@{u}Tooltypes/Shell Arguments@{uu}

PREFS/K         Used to define another path or filename for the prefs file.
                By default, MidiTracker will try to load a file called
                MidiTracker.prefs in its home directory.

ICONIFY/S       If enabled MidiTracker will start in an iconified state. 
                You may select your favorite hiding method from within the
                @{" System Preferences " link "sysprefs"}.

MAXTRACKS/N/K   This tells MidiTracker how many tracks to use in each
                instrument. Only 6 tracks can be viewed on screen at once.
                Minimum = 6 
                Maximum = 32767
                Default = 8
                The lower the MAXTRACKS-value, the faster MidiTracker will
                switch between instruments.

@Endnode
@Node "mt-mc-ed" "MidiTracker Controlsource Editor"

@{u}MidiTracker Midi-Controlsource Editor@{uu}

This program is written by Alexander M. Korn. Thank you!

You may edit the "Controlsources" file using this utility.

@Endnode
