@Node "bugs" "Bugreports"

Please SAVE YOUR SONGS REGULARLY!!!!!!!!!  MidiTracker is constantly being
tested for new bugs, but hopefully I have found most of the fatal ones. :-) 
If for some reason MidiTracker does fall over, it's better that you do not
lose too much of your hard work.

I would suggest you save your songs as different versions ie 'the song1.mt'
'the song2.mt' ... etc that way you always have a history of versions to go
back to if something goes wrong.

@{u}Known Bugs@{uu}

- Sample processor crashes sometimes when editing a sample at its end
- MidiTracker may guru if you quit it (very rare)

@{u}What to do if *gasp* MidiTracker falls over?@{uu}

When encountering a bug or a broken or missing feature feel free to 
@{" let me know " link "author"}. To maximize the chance of me finding the bug please 
include the following information :

  - your computer (if it has changed from the configuration on your
    ordering-form)
  - MIDI equipment (synths/keyboards/drum machines/...) and midi-setup
  - prefs-file (MidiTracker.prefs), or your song
  - your version of MidiTracker

@Endnode
