@Node "register" "Welcome to the family"

@{u}Becoming a registered MidiTracker user@{uu}

When I have received the shareware fee I will send you the keyfile which
will activate all the @{" dead features " link "limit"} of the shareware version. Just copy your
personal keyfile into MidiTracker's directory and you're away!  You can
choose between receiving the keyfile via disk or by email.

The shareware amount is DM 50 or US $35.00. Please contact me if can't pay
in either currency.

Please take some time to fill out the registration form correctly so I put
the right information into you keyfile. Please print it out and include it
with your letter as this is the only way I will accept registrations. Also
make sure you sign it before sending it to me as it tells me you agree to
the terms and conditions as in the @{" legal info " link "legal"} section.


@{u}Cash@{uu} or @{u}Euro-cheque@{uu}

Send a letter to my @{" address " link "author"} with the money or a cheque in it.

@{u}Bank transfer@{uu}

Tell me when you have transferred the money to my bank account given
below. When I confirm the deposit with my bank, I will send you the
keyfile. Please don't forget to send the registration form.

Citibank Privatkunden AG, Bank 30020900, Bank code 2606720092


@{u}The Australian Registration Site@{uu}

If you are living in Australia or New Zealand, you should order the keyfile
from Scott Watson. Send the registration form and either :-

- AUS $50 for keyfile via regular mail on disk
- AUS $45 for keyfile via email

@{u}Mail Address@{uu}

Scott Watson
124 Copperfield Street
Geebung, 4034
Queensland
Australia

@{u}E-Mail Address@{uu}

sjw@mailbox.uq.edu.au

@Endnode
@Node "history" "About the past"

@{u}Version History@{uu}

@{u}V1.2@{uu}

- Midi prefs: Removed "Player Priority" gadget.
  The "Ignore Note-Offs" gadget and the "Auto rewind" gadget (main window)
  have exchanged their places.

- System-prefs: Midi access with Midi-Lib available!
  (Play samples with a sample-player program!)

- PC Keyboard option

- Metronome: Bank input, Record button, Test button, Count-In-Only option.

- Channelscope: New HiFi-look and peak-hold

- Sysex-Editor

- Main menu: Quickloader

- Block invert/shift/flip functions

- Export SMF Type-1 files.

- Main window trackdisplay changes:
  1) Tempo value is now with two decimal places!
  2) Preset column has now 6 digits (instead of 3): Bank + Program.
  3) The two Polypressure digits are removed from the note-tracks.
     There's a new cycle-gadget which you can toggle between
     velocity and polypressure.

- Synth support for: QuasiMIDI Quasar
                     Roland MC-303
                     Yamaha-XG
                     Yamaha CS1x

- Editable preset-names for the supported synths

- Editable controlsources (name + reset value)

- When playing a song (from any position), MT will trace back the
  controlsources and tempo changes.


@{u}V1.1.1@{uu}

- Emergency update release: there was a bug which caused a crash if the
  system prefs window was opened and a song was loaded.

- Boehm Dynamic 12/24 Expander support


@{u}V1.1@{uu}


Bugfixes:

- Fixed a few missing links in the documentation

- Have removed the auto note off ability when playing notes via the amiga
  keyboard as it was causing more problems than it solved. Use "`" to enter
  note offs in edit mode.

- The first listview entry of a dialog window was missing when reopening
  the window.

- The Screenmode-Autoscroll bug is fixed.

- A channel's resolution couldn't be changed while playing.

- Channelscope-levels will now raise to remapped channels.


New features:

- Added the @{" Keyboard Actions Window " link "keyboardactions"}

- New in System prefs: Clock checkbox, to disable title clock.

- Sample Dump window has now a SysEx-ID entry field.

- The Sample Dump window titlebar is showing the dump progress in bytes.

- In main window, the "Quantize" gadget is renamed as "Edit Step".

- In midi-prefs window, a new, third midi-mode called "Channel" has appeared.

- MT is now able to import OctaMED MMD1 modules.

- MT is now able to import GM-type-1 files.

- System prefs: Switch to disable title clock.
  (For people using a pubscreen title bar clock commodity.)

- The Stacker/Remapper is not disabled when MT is unregistered. It can be
  used and evaluated because it seems to be an important feature.

- Block-randomize function (in Block-menu)

- Tempo BPM values from 1-27 are also allowed.

- Score window layout and functionality has changed totally.

- SysEx window implemented: Allows recording/sending SysEx messages
  to midi. Can also load/save messages.

- MIDI In/Out Filter window implemented.


@{u}V1.0@{uu}

- First release

@Endnode
