@Node "todo" "What is up next?"

@{u}The future - What can you expect?@{uu}

Here's a list of features that MidiTracker may contain some day. You can
encourage me if you want one of these features urgently :-)

 - Executable player for MT-songs to use for multimedia projects
 - miditracker.library so your own programs can play MT-songs
 - Amiga-sample metronome (in case you don't want it on midi)
 - Iconify-method: AppIcon
 - Post record quantization (editmode) + undo
 - Record from the amiga-keyboard ?
 - Sample editor: Paste and Mix functions
 - Song arrangement window
 - Groove quantize ?
 - Resolution-zoom window
 - Multi level undo/redo
 - Mark-block with mouse
 - Drag'n'drop
 - Save icons
 - Save backups and timed autosave function
 - Mark multiple tracks but not entire instrument
 - Decimal entry for hex fields
 - Flush instrument = clear an instrument for the entire song
 - Automatic mastervolume fader
 - Turn off Amiga keyboard entry and remap hotkeys without qualifiers
 - Quantize controlsources
 - pOS version


This is just a sample of the things on my todo list, so as you can see
MidiTracker definitely has room for more features.

Do *you* have any ideas for a new feature in MidiTracker?!  @{" Let me know " link "author"} 
of your ideas..

If you are missing a catalog file in your preferred language and are
interested in writing one, please @{" contact me " link "author"}. 

@Endnode
